<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!-- Bharat unique units, wave 2 (Chat-project alternate-history design,
     ranked shortlist): Rani of Jhansi Regiment (ranged), Azad Hind Nau Sena
     (naval), Bahadur Group (recon-style supplemental). Same wiring pattern as
     the Stage-2 Azad Hind Fauj in data/bharat-units.xml (Types + Units +
     Stats/Costs + UnitReplaces + class-tag -> UnitClass_Abilities ->
     UnitAbilityModifiers one-hop ability grant; modifiers live in
     data/bharat-units-2-gameeffects.xml).

     RANI OF JHANSI REGIMENT — replaces UNIT_MORTAR (the Modern tier-1 ranged
     land line; stats 40/35/55 range 2, cost 260 mirrored exactly from
     age-modern/data/units.xml). ONE deliberate deviation: UNIT_MOVEMENT_CLASS_
     FOOT instead of Mortar's WHEELED — this is a rifle regiment, not a towed
     piece. Design's "+5 when defending" had no engine requirement (no
     REQUIREMENT_UNIT_IS_DEFENDER exists); per the design's own fallback note
     the effect maps to the PROVEN home-ground condition at Cossack's exact
     magnitude: +4 Combat Strength in friendly territory
     (COSSACK_MOD_COMBAT_STRENGTH_IN_FRIENDLY_TERRITORY pattern verbatim).
     The thematic mirror of the Fauj: the Fauj liberates abroad (+1 outside),
     the Regiment guards home.

     AZAD HIND NAU SENA — replaces UNIT_DESTROYER (Tier 3 naval escort; stats
     55/30/30 range 1, cost 400 mirrored exactly). +3 Combat Strength in
     friendly territory (same proven requirement set, design's number).

     BAHADUR GROUP — SUPPLEMENTAL light recon infantry (no Modern recon line
     exists to replace — UNIT_EXPLORER is civilian — so no UnitReplaces row,
     per the design's fallback). Light, fast, far-seeing: Combat 35, Moves 3,
     Sight 3, cost 200, exerts no ZOC itself and IGNORES enemy ZOC
     (EFFECT_ADJUST_UNIT_IGNORE_ZOC — SWIFT_MOD_UNIT_IGNORE_ZOC pattern
     verbatim, base-standard/data/units-gameeffects.xml:128). -->
